States of America, Uruguay (also on behalf of Argentina, Bolivia (Plurinational State of), 
Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, Paraguay and Venezuela (Bolivarian Republic of)); 
</p>
<p>(b) Representatives of the following observer States: Algeria, Australia, C&#244;te 
d&#8217;Ivoire; 
</p>
<p>(c) Observer for United Nations entities, specialized agencies and related 
organizations: United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees; 
</p>
<p>(d) Observer for a national human rights institution: Consultative Council of 
Human Rights of Morocco; 
</p>
<p>(e) Observers for the following non-governmental organizations: International 
Commission of Jurists, Migrants Rights International (also on behalf of the International 
Detention Coalition, the Migrant Forum in Asia and the National Network for Immigrant 
and Refugee Rights), World Organization against Torture. 
</p>
<p>90. At the same meeting, the following panellists answered questions and made 
comments: Abdelhamid El Jamri, Vanessa Lesnie and Ashley William Bonaventure Gois. 
</p>
